{"title_page": "Nepalis", "text_new": "{{pp-move|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{more references|date=April 2020}}\n'''Nepalis''' (singular:'''Nepali''', synonym:'''Nepalese'''; {{lang-ne|\u0928\u0947\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0940}}) are the people associated with the country of [[Nepal]]. The term usually refers to the [[Nepali nationality law|citizens]] and nationals of Nepal, or the native speakers of the Nepali language. It is also used in reference to the people of Nepali origin or of ethnicities strongly associated with Nepal irrespective of their citizenship or native language.\n\n==Nepali citizens and nationals==\nNepali nationals number around 30 Million, with six million of them residing in India,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indembkathmandu.gov.in/page/about-india-nepal-relations/|title=Embassy of India, Kathmandu, Nepal : About India-Nepal Relations|website=www.indembkathmandu.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> and one million more scattered around the world. They are multicultural, multiethnic and multilinguistic group that speak [[Languages of Nepal|123 languages]] as recorded in [[2011 Nepal census]].\n\nThe population ranking of 125 Nepali castes/ethnic groups as per the [[2011 Nepal census]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://unstats.un.org/unsD/demographic/sources/census/wphc/Nepal/Nepal-Census-2011-Vol1.pdf|title=Nepal Census 2011}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align: right;\"\n! style=\"text-align:left\" | Rank\n! Caste/ethnic groups\n! Population\n! Percentage composition\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 1\n| [[Chhetri]]\n| 4,398,053\n| 16.60%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 2\n| [[Bahun|Hill Brahman/Bahun]]\n| 3,226,903\n| 12.18%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 3\n| [[Magar people|Magar]]\n| 1,887,733\n| 7.12%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 4\n| [[Tharu people|Tharu]]\n| 1,737,470\n| 6.56%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 5\n| [[Tamang people|Tamang]]\n| 1,539,830\n| 5.81%\n|-\n| style=\"text-ali