 million in India, and about a million more including populations in Bhutan and other countries in the region, as well as the Nepalese diaspora around the world. \n\n==Others==\nOther people who are neither citizens or nationals of Nepal nor native speakers of the Nepali language, may still be referred to as Nepalis, based on their connection with the country or the Nepali language. The people belonging to ethnicities found in Nepal and using Nepali as the lingua franca, and other descendants of the people of Nepal or speakers of the Nepali language are also referred to as Nepalis.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Languages of Nepal]]\n* [[List of Nepali people]]\n* [[Music of Nepal]]\n* [[Religion in Nepal]]\n{{notelist}}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Nepalese people| ]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups divided by international borders]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Nepal|.]]\n[[Category:Ethno-cultural designations]]\n[[Category:Gurkhas|.]]\n\n\n{{Nepal-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{pp-move|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{more references|date=April 2020}}\n'''Nepalis''' (singular:'''Nepali''', synonym:'''Nepalese'''; {{lang-ne|\u0928\u0947\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0940}}) are the people associated with the country of [[Nepal]]. The term usually refers to the [[Nepali nationality law|citizens]] and nationals of Nepal, or the native speakers of the Nepali language. It is also used in reference to the people of Nepali origin or of ethnicities strongly associated with Nepal irrespective of their citizenship or native language.\n\n==Nepali citizens and nationals==\nNepali nationals number around 30 Million, with six million of them residing in India,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indembkathmandu.gov.in/page/about-india-nepal-relations/|title=Embassy of India, Kathmandu, Nepal : About India-Nepal Relations|website=www.indembkathmandu.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> and one million more scattered around the world. They are multicultural, multiethnic and multiling